==Korean==
===Verb===
'''기르다''' (''gireuda'')
# (''transitive'') To '''[[grow]]''', [[raise]], [[breed]], [[cultivate]], [[foster]], [[nurse]], [[bring up]]
# (''transitive'') To [[build up]], [[develop]]

====Synonyms====
*[[키우다]] (''kiuda'') (''transitive'') (''literally, to make big'') To [[grow]]

====Antonyms====
*[[버리다]] (''beorida'') To [[throw away]], [[abandon]], [[desert]], [[give up]] 
*[[줄이다]] (''jurIda'') To [[shorten]], [[lessen]], [[decrease]], [[reduce]]
*[[죽이다]] (''jugIda'') To [[kill]]

====Derived terms====
*[[길러]] [[주다]] (''gilleo juda'') To  [[grow]], help or make [[grow]], [[nurse]], [[foster]], [[train]]

====Related terms====
*[[길다]] (''gilda'') (''adjective'') To be [[long]]
*[[길이]] ('girI'') [[length]]
*[[길]] (''gil, gir'') [[way]], [[path]], [[road]]
*[[길들이다]] (''gildeurIda'') To [[polish]]; [[tame]], [[train]], [[accustom]], [[domesticate]], [[indoctrinate]] (''Note: The first syllable 'gil' is a noun meaning "[[way]], [[path]]; [[custom]], [[rule]], [[progress]], [[indoctrination]]".'')  
*[[자라다]] (''jarada'') (''intransitive'') To [[grow]]
*[[크다]] (''keuda'') (''intransitive'') To [[grow]]; (''adjective'') to be '''[[great]]''', [[big]], [[tall]]
*[[크기]] (''keugi'') [[size]], [[magnitude]]
*[[키]] (''ki'') [[height]]

